=head2 SegmentAttributes => L<Paws::Connect::SegmentAttributes>

A set of system defined key-value pairs stored on individual contact
segments using an attribute map. The attributes are standard Amazon
Connect attributes and can be accessed in flows. Attribute keys can
include only alphanumeric, -, and _ characters. This field can be used
to show channel subtype. For example, C<connect:Guide> or
C<connect:SMS>.


=head2 SystemEndpoint => L<Paws::Connect::EndpointInfo>

The system endpoint. For C<INBOUND>, this is the phone number or email
address that the customer dialed. For C<OUTBOUND> and
C<EXTERNAL_OUTBOUND>, this is the outbound caller ID number assigned to
the outbound queue that is used to dial the customer. For callback,
this shows up as Softphone for calls handled by agents with softphone.


